@node %EinfÅhrungV "Preface"
@toc Introduction
@symbol Preface
@xref Installation
@autorefoff
Introduction, Preface                                                 Thing
@line 1 75 0 0 7
@autorefon

The german version of Thing was released for the first time in
december 1994. Since then many additional features where invented and
many suggestions from users where implemented. The big number of registered
users and articles in 'ST-Computer', 'Atari World' and 'ST Format'
motivated me to continue the development of Thing ;-)

The current version is now 'real' shareware with key and some very little
restrictions.

The hypertext documentation was completely re-written (the new release 14
of ST-Guide was one reason to do this ;-)). You should use ST-Guide
release 14 or newer -- as only this version provides the 'see also...'-
button.

Some links in this document are references to other hypertext files. These
files should also be installed in the GUIDES folder of ST-Guide:

  ST-GUIDE.HYP ... the documentation of ST-Guide
  TOS2GEM.HYP .... the documentation of TOS2GEM from Thomas Binder
  AIP.HYP ........ Atari Info Pages from Manfred Ssykor
                   (Release 8 or newer)

Here you can try it out:  @{"ST-Guide in the Atari Info Pages" link aip.hyp/ST-Guide}


@line 10 55 0 0 7


An overview about the features of Thing:

 ˘ Context sensitive help with ST-Guide: You can get help by pressing the
@box 4 6 1
    Help -key. In a multitasking environment, ST-Guide can be used as an
   external program too.

 ˘ Full support of alternate file systems: Thing supports long,
   case-sensitive file names up to 32 characters length.

 ˘ Support of TOSWIN under MiNT - so you can run TOS/TTP programs parallel
   to the desktop even with Single-TOS.

 ˘ Console Window using TOS2GEM from Thomas Binder. All features of TOS2GEM
   are well supported.

 ˘ Support of Let'em Fly, WINX, Freedom and Space.

 ˘ Kobold support: Kobold 2 can be used for copying/moving/deleting files
   and formatting disks. You can use Kobold as an accessory or as an
   external program. You can specify the minimum number of files or the
   amount of data for Kobold usage.

 ˘ GEM-IMG-files can be used as background pictures for the desktop.

 ˘ Full GDOS support: Even proporitional fonts and all kind of TrueType-
   and Speedo-fonts can be used for directory windows.

 ˘ Full AV protocol: Most of the tools, which where designed for use
   with Gemini can be used with Thing too (e.g. ParaFin, PacShell or
   TreeView).

 ˘ Font protocol from Christian Grunenberg: Thing can be used as a
   'font selector' -- 'active' by using the FONT_SELECT-message or
   via 'Drag&Drop' (Thing sends FONT_CHANGED to the owner of the window).

 ˘ Drag&Drop protocol with MultiTOS or MagiC!3.

 ˘ 'Modern' dialog boxes in windows, non-modal and with keyboard-shortcuts.
   'Tabs', 'Drop-Down-Listboxes' and 3D-buttons where also implemented.

 ˘ Icons at any size in a normal GEM resource file. Colour icons (up to
   16 colours) and 'animated' icons are supported as well.

 ˘ 'Object groups' to hold several file, folders and programs in common
   windows -- similar to a 'desktop in a window'.
@endnode

