@node %EinfÅhrungCON "Console Window"
@toc Introduction
@symbol "Console Window"
@autorefoff
Introduction, Console Window                                          Thing
@line 1 75 0 0 7
@autorefon

The utility TOS2GEM, programmed by Thomas Binder offers a clean and
simple scrolling window to displays the output from TOS/TTP programs.

TOS2GEM is only reserved if the window is open. Otherwise other
programs may also use TOS2GEM for their own needs.

Under a multitasking environment it's important to note that every
other application, including Thing itself, is blocked when the Console
window is in operation.

TOS programs do not run in parallel with thing, when started in
the Thing console window.

In order to run TOS/TTP programs in parallel with regular GEM
applications there are various tools supplied with MagiC and/or
MultiTOS (VT52, MINIWIN). These are automatically started by the
operating system so long as a TOS/TTP program has not been started in
the Thing console window.


@{U}Terminal size@{0}

If the environmental variables LINES and COLUMNS are set, Thing sets
the terminal size to the specified values. Otherwise, the terminal inside
the console window will be 25 lines and 80 coloumns.


@autorefoff
@{U}History@{0}

If you want to see long outputs of program (e.g. compiler etc.) after
leaving the program, you can specify a 'history buffer' up to 9999 lines.
The beginning of this buffer is marked with a horizontal line.
You can change the size of the history buffer in the page 'TOS2GEM' of
the 'Setup' dialog.

If you do not need a history buffer, you should set the history to 0 lines
to save memory.
@autorefon
@endnode

